.\" Manpage for bitcoin(1).
.TH BITCOIN 1 "May 2026" "scripts" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bitcoin \- educational Bitcoin frontend (BIPs implemented end-to-end)

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bitcoin
.RI [ options ]
.I command
.RI [ args ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bitcoin
is the educational Bitcoin frontend. Each subcommand
implements a specific BIP (Bitcoin Improvement Proposal),
cites the spec in its help text, and points at the
vendored reference under
.IR share/doc/bitcoin/standards/
(FEAT-017).

The wallet model:

.IP \(bu 2
The seed phrase lives in
.BR secret (1)
\(em not in
.BR bitcoin .
.IP \(bu 2
Address derivation reads the seed via
.B "secret get <wallet>/seed"
on demand.
.IP \(bu 2
Same address use is acceptable; no privacy-leak
warning is emitted.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS

.SS BIP plugins (libexec/bitcoin/<name>)

.TP
.B bip13
Pay-to-Script-Hash address encoding.
.TP
.B bip32
Hierarchical deterministic wallet derivation.
.TP
.B bip39
Mnemonic seed phrase encoding.
.TP
.B wif
Wallet Import Format private key encoding.
.TP
.B daemon
Multi-backend daemon abstraction
(bitcoind / mempool.space / blockstream.info).

.SS Wallet (FEAT-018, partial)

.TP
.BI "wallet new " name
Create a new wallet (seed phrase stored in
.BR secret ).
.TP
.BI "wallet derive " name " " path
Derive an address at the given BIP-32 path.
.TP
.BI "wallet balance " name
Query balance via the configured daemon.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SELF_DEBUG
Enable shell tracing.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I libexec/bitcoin/<plugin>
Per-BIP plugin script.
.TP
.I share/doc/bitcoin/standards/
Vendored BIP source documents (FEAT-017).

.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success; non-zero on failure.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR account (1),
.BR secret (1),
.BR lightning (1),
.BR bitcoind (8).

.SH STANDARDS
BIP 13 (P2SH), BIP 32 (HD wallets), BIP 39 (mnemonic),
BIP 173 (bech32 addresses) \(em vendored under
.IR share/doc/bitcoin/standards/ .

.SH BUGS
Report at
.UR https://github.com/nostra124/scripts/issues
.UE .
